3977 def infer_variable_type(
3978 self, name: Var, lvalue: Lvalue, init_type: Type, context: Context
3979 ) -> None:
3980 """Infer the type of initialized variables from initializer type."""
3981 if isinstance(init_type, DeletedType):
3982 self.msg.deleted_as_rvalue(init_type, context)
3983 elif (
3984 not is_valid_inferred_type(init_type, is_lvalue_final=name.is_final)
3985 and not self.no_partial_types
3986 ):
3987 # We cannot use the type of the initialization expression for full type
3988 # inference (it's not specific enough), but we might be able to give
3989 # partial type which will be made more specific later. A partial type
3990 # gets generated in assignment like 'x = []' where item type is not known.
3991 if not self.infer_partial_type(name, lvalue, init_type):
3992 self.msg.need_annotation_for_var(name, context, self.options.python_version)
3993 self.set_inference_error_fallback_type(name, lvalue, init_type)
3994 elif (
3995 isinstance(lvalue, MemberExpr)
3996 and self.inferred_attribute_types is not None
3997 and lvalue.def_var
3998 and lvalue.def_var in self.inferred_attribute_types
3999 and not is_same_type(self.inferred_attribute_types[lvalue.def_var], init_type)
4000 ):
4001 # Multiple, inconsistent types inferred for an attribute.
4002 self.msg.need_annotation_for_var(name, context, self.options.python_version)
4003 name.type = AnyType(TypeOfAny.from_error)
4004 else:
4005 # Infer type of the target.
4006  
4007 # Make the type more general (strip away function names etc.).
4008 init_type = strip_type(init_type)
4009  
4010 self.set_inferred_type(name, lvalue, init_type)
4011  
4012 def infer_partial_type(self, name: Var, lvalue: Lvalue, init_type: Type) -> bool:
4013 init_type = get_proper_type(init_type)
4014 if isinstance(init_type, NoneType):
4015 partial_type = PartialType(None, name)
4016 elif isinstance(init_type, Instance):
4017 fullname = init_type.type.fullname
4018 is_ref = isinstance(lvalue, RefExpr)
4019 if (
4020 is_ref
4021 and (
4022 fullname == "builtins.list"
4023 or fullname == "builtins.set"
4024 or fullname == "builtins.dict"
4025 or fullname == "collections.OrderedDict"
4026 )
4027 and all(
4028 isinstance(t, (NoneType, UninhabitedType))
4029 for t in get_proper_types(init_type.args)
4030 )
4031 ):
4032 partial_type = PartialType(init_type.type, name)
4033 elif is_ref and fullname == "collections.defaultdict":
4034 arg0 = get_proper_type(init_type.args[0])
4035 arg1 = get_proper_type(init_type.args[1])
4036 if isinstance(
4037 arg0, (NoneType, UninhabitedType)
4038 ) and self.is_valid_defaultdict_partial_value_type(arg1):
4039 arg1 = erase_type(arg1)
4040 assert isinstance(arg1, Instance)
4041 partial_type = PartialType(init_type.type, name, arg1)
4042 else:
4043 return False
4044 else:
4045 return False
4046 else:
4047 return False
4048 self.set_inferred_type(name, lvalue, partial_type)
4049 self.partial_types[-1].map[name] = lvalue
4050 return True
4051  
4052 def is_valid_defaultdict_partial_value_type(self, t: ProperType) -> bool:
4053 """Check if t can be used as the basis for a partial defaultdict value type.
4054  
4055 Examples:
4056  
4057 * t is 'int' --> True
4058 * t is 'list[Never]' --> True
4059 * t is 'dict[...]' --> False (only generic types with a single type
4060 argument supported)
4061 """
4062 if not isinstance(t, Instance):
4063 return False
4064 if len(t.args) == 0:
4065 return True
4066 if len(t.args) == 1:
4067 arg = get_proper_type(t.args[0])
4068 if self.options.old_type_inference:
4069 # Allow leaked TypeVars for legacy inference logic.
4070 allowed = isinstance(arg, (UninhabitedType, NoneType, TypeVarType))
4071 else:
4072 allowed = isinstance(arg, (UninhabitedType, NoneType))
4073 if allowed:
4074 return True
4075 return False

4077 def set_inferred_type(self, var: Var, lvalue: Lvalue, type: Type) -> None:
4078 """Store inferred variable type.
4079  
4080 Store the type to both the variable node and the expression node that
4081 refers to the variable (lvalue). If var is None, do nothing.
4082 """
4083 if var and not self.current_node_deferred:
4084 var.type = type
4085 var.is_inferred = True
4086 if var not in self.var_decl_frames:
4087 # Used for the hack to improve optional type inference in conditionals
4088 self.var_decl_frames[var] = {frame.id for frame in self.binder.frames}
4089 if isinstance(lvalue, MemberExpr) and self.inferred_attribute_types is not None:
4090 # Store inferred attribute type so that we can check consistency afterwards.
4091 if lvalue.def_var is not None:
4092 self.inferred_attribute_types[lvalue.def_var] = type
4093 self.store_type(lvalue, type)
4094  
4095 def set_inference_error_fallback_type(self, var: Var, lvalue: Lvalue, type: Type) -> None:
4096 """Store best known type for variable if type inference failed.
4097  
4098 If a program ignores error on type inference error, the variable should get some
4099 inferred type so that if can used later on in the program. Example:
4100  
4101 x = [] # type: ignore
4102 x.append(1) # Should be ok!
4103  
4104 We implement this here by giving x a valid type (replacing inferred Never with Any).
4105 """
4106 fallback = self.inference_error_fallback_type(type)
4107 self.set_inferred_type(var, lvalue, fallback)
4108  
4109 def inference_error_fallback_type(self, type: Type) -> Type:
4110 fallback = type.accept(SetNothingToAny())
4111 # Type variables may leak from inference, see https://github.com/python/mypy/issues/5738,
4112 # we therefore need to erase them.
4113 return erase_typevars(fallback)
4114  
4115 def simple_rvalue(self, rvalue: Expression) -> bool:
4116 """Returns True for expressions for which inferred type should not depend on context.
4117  
4118 Note that this function can still return False for some expressions where inferred type
4119 does not depend on context. It only exists for performance optimizations.
4120 """
4121 if isinstance(rvalue, (IntExpr, StrExpr, BytesExpr, FloatExpr, RefExpr)):
4122 return True
4123 if isinstance(rvalue, CallExpr):
4124 if isinstance(rvalue.callee, RefExpr) and isinstance(rvalue.callee.node, FuncBase):
4125 typ = rvalue.callee.node.type
4126 if isinstance(typ, CallableType):
4127 return not typ.variables
4128 elif isinstance(typ, Overloaded):
4129 return not any(item.variables for item in typ.items)
4130 return False

4132 def check_simple_assignment(
4133 self,
4134 lvalue_type: Type | None,
4135 rvalue: Expression,
4136 context: Context,
4137 msg: ErrorMessage = message_registry.INCOMPATIBLE_TYPES_IN_ASSIGNMENT,
4138 lvalue_name: str = "variable",
4139 rvalue_name: str = "expression",
4140 *,
4141 notes: list[str] | None = None,
4142 ) -> Type:
4143 if self.is_stub and isinstance(rvalue, EllipsisExpr):
4144 # '...' is always a valid initializer in a stub.
4145 return AnyType(TypeOfAny.special_form)
4146 else:
4147 always_allow_any = lvalue_type is not None and not isinstance(
4148 get_proper_type(lvalue_type), AnyType
4149 )
4150 rvalue_type = self.expr_checker.accept(
4151 rvalue, lvalue_type, always_allow_any=always_allow_any
4152 )
4153 if (
4154 isinstance(get_proper_type(lvalue_type), UnionType)
4155 # Skip literal types, as they have special logic (for better errors).
4156 and not isinstance(get_proper_type(rvalue_type), LiteralType)
4157 and not self.simple_rvalue(rvalue)
4158 ):
4159 # Try re-inferring r.h.s. in empty context, and use that if it
4160 # results in a narrower type. We don't do this always because this
4161 # may cause some perf impact, plus we want to partially preserve
4162 # the old behavior. This helps with various practical examples, see
4163 # e.g. testOptionalTypeNarrowedByGenericCall.
4164 with self.msg.filter_errors() as local_errors, self.local_type_map() as type_map:
4165 alt_rvalue_type = self.expr_checker.accept(
4166 rvalue, None, always_allow_any=always_allow_any
4167 )
4168 if (
4169 not local_errors.has_new_errors()
4170 # Skip Any type, since it is special cased in binder.
4171 and not isinstance(get_proper_type(alt_rvalue_type), AnyType)
4172 and is_valid_inferred_type(alt_rvalue_type)
4173 and is_proper_subtype(alt_rvalue_type, rvalue_type)
4174 ):
4175 rvalue_type = alt_rvalue_type
4176 self.store_types(type_map)
4177 if isinstance(rvalue_type, DeletedType):
4178 self.msg.deleted_as_rvalue(rvalue_type, context)
4179 if isinstance(lvalue_type, DeletedType):
4180 self.msg.deleted_as_lvalue(lvalue_type, context)
4181 elif lvalue_type:
4182 self.check_subtype(
4183 # Preserve original aliases for error messages when possible.
4184 rvalue_type,
4185 lvalue_type,
4186 context,
4187 msg,
4188 f"{rvalue_name} has type",
4189 f"{lvalue_name} has type",
4190 notes=notes,
4191 )
4192 return rvalue_type
4193  
4194 def check_member_assignment(
4195 self, instance_type: Type, attribute_type: Type, rvalue: Expression, context: Context
4196 ) -> tuple[Type, Type, bool]:
4197 """Type member assignment.
4198  
4199 This defers to check_simple_assignment, unless the member expression
4200 is a descriptor, in which case this checks descriptor semantics as well.
4201  
4202 Return the inferred rvalue_type, inferred lvalue_type, and whether to use the binder
4203 for this assignment.
4204  
4205 Note: this method exists here and not in checkmember.py, because we need to take
4206 care about interaction between binder and __set__().
4207 """
4208 instance_type = get_proper_type(instance_type)
4209 attribute_type = get_proper_type(attribute_type)
4210 # Descriptors don't participate in class-attribute access
4211 if (isinstance(instance_type, FunctionLike) and instance_type.is_type_obj()) or isinstance(
4212 instance_type, TypeType
4213 ):
4214 rvalue_type = self.check_simple_assignment(attribute_type, rvalue, context)
4215 return rvalue_type, attribute_type, True
4216  
4217 if not isinstance(attribute_type, Instance):
4218 # TODO: support __set__() for union types.
4219 rvalue_type = self.check_simple_assignment(attribute_type, rvalue, context)
4220 return rvalue_type, attribute_type, True
4221  
4222 mx = MemberContext(
4223 is_lvalue=False,
4224 is_super=False,
4225 is_operator=False,
4226 original_type=instance_type,
4227 context=context,
4228 self_type=None,
4229 msg=self.msg,
4230 chk=self,
4231 )
4232 get_type = analyze_descriptor_access(attribute_type, mx)
4233 if not attribute_type.type.has_readable_member("__set__"):
4234 # If there is no __set__, we type-check that the assigned value matches
4235 # the return type of __get__. This doesn't match the python semantics,
4236 # (which allow you to override the descriptor with any value), but preserves
4237 # the type of accessing the attribute (even after the override).
4238 rvalue_type = self.check_simple_assignment(get_type, rvalue, context)
4239 return rvalue_type, get_type, True
4240  
4241 dunder_set = attribute_type.type.get_method("__set__")
4242 if dunder_set is None:
4243 self.fail(
4244 message_registry.DESCRIPTOR_SET_NOT_CALLABLE.format(
4245 attribute_type.str_with_options(self.options)
4246 ),
4247 context,
4248 )
4249 return AnyType(TypeOfAny.from_error), get_type, False
4250  
4251 bound_method = analyze_decorator_or_funcbase_access(
4252 defn=dunder_set,
4253 itype=attribute_type,
4254 info=attribute_type.type,
4255 self_type=attribute_type,
4256 name="__set__",
4257 mx=mx,
4258 )
4259 typ = map_instance_to_supertype(attribute_type, dunder_set.info)
4260 dunder_set_type = expand_type_by_instance(bound_method, typ)
4261  
4262 callable_name = self.expr_checker.method_fullname(attribute_type, "__set__")
4263 dunder_set_type = self.expr_checker.transform_callee_type(
4264 callable_name,
4265 dunder_set_type,
4266 [TempNode(instance_type, context=context), rvalue],
4267 [nodes.ARG_POS, nodes.ARG_POS],
4268 context,
4269 object_type=attribute_type,
4270 )
4271  
4272 # For non-overloaded setters, the result should be type-checked like a regular assignment.
4273 # Hence, we first only try to infer the type by using the rvalue as type context.
4274 type_context = rvalue
4275 with self.msg.filter_errors():
4276 _, inferred_dunder_set_type = self.expr_checker.check_call(
4277 dunder_set_type,
4278 [TempNode(instance_type, context=context), type_context],
4279 [nodes.ARG_POS, nodes.ARG_POS],
4280 context,
4281 object_type=attribute_type,
4282 callable_name=callable_name,
4283 )
4284  
4285 # And now we in fact type check the call, to show errors related to wrong arguments
4286 # count, etc., replacing the type context for non-overloaded setters only.
4287 inferred_dunder_set_type = get_proper_type(inferred_dunder_set_type)
4288 if isinstance(inferred_dunder_set_type, CallableType):
4289 type_context = TempNode(AnyType(TypeOfAny.special_form), context=context)
4290 self.expr_checker.check_call(
4291 dunder_set_type,
4292 [TempNode(instance_type, context=context), type_context],
4293 [nodes.ARG_POS, nodes.ARG_POS],
4294 context,
4295 object_type=attribute_type,
4296 callable_name=callable_name,
4297 )
4298  
4299 # In the following cases, a message already will have been recorded in check_call.
4300 if (not isinstance(inferred_dunder_set_type, CallableType)) or (
4301 len(inferred_dunder_set_type.arg_types) < 2
4302 ):
4303 return AnyType(TypeOfAny.from_error), get_type, False
4304  
4305 set_type = inferred_dunder_set_type.arg_types[1]
4306 # Special case: if the rvalue_type is a subtype of both '__get__' and '__set__' types,
4307 # and '__get__' type is narrower than '__set__', then we invoke the binder to narrow type
4308 # by this assignment. Technically, this is not safe, but in practice this is
4309 # what a user expects.
4310 rvalue_type = self.check_simple_assignment(set_type, rvalue, context)
4311 infer = is_subtype(rvalue_type, get_type) and is_subtype(get_type, set_type)
4312 return rvalue_type if infer else set_type, get_type, infer
4313  
4314 def check_indexed_assignment(
4315 self, lvalue: IndexExpr, rvalue: Expression, context: Context
4316 ) -> None:
4317 """Type check indexed assignment base[index] = rvalue.
4318  
4319 The lvalue argument is the base[index] expression.
4320 """
4321 self.try_infer_partial_type_from_indexed_assignment(lvalue, rvalue)
4322 basetype = get_proper_type(self.expr_checker.accept(lvalue.base))
4323 method_type = self.expr_checker.analyze_external_member_access(
4324 "__setitem__", basetype, lvalue
4325 )
4326  
4327 lvalue.method_type = method_type
4328 res_type, _ = self.expr_checker.check_method_call(
4329 "__setitem__",
4330 basetype,
4331 method_type,
4332 [lvalue.index, rvalue],
4333 [nodes.ARG_POS, nodes.ARG_POS],
4334 context,
4335 )
4336 res_type = get_proper_type(res_type)
4337 if isinstance(res_type, UninhabitedType) and not res_type.ambiguous:
4338 self.binder.unreachable()
4339  
4340 def try_infer_partial_type_from_indexed_assignment(
4341 self, lvalue: IndexExpr, rvalue: Expression
4342 ) -> None:
4343 # TODO: Should we share some of this with try_infer_partial_type?
4344 var = None
4345 if isinstance(lvalue.base, RefExpr) and isinstance(lvalue.base.node, Var):
4346 var = lvalue.base.node
4347 elif isinstance(lvalue.base, MemberExpr):
4348 var = self.expr_checker.get_partial_self_var(lvalue.base)
4349 if isinstance(var, Var):
4350 if isinstance(var.type, PartialType):
4351 type_type = var.type.type
4352 if type_type is None:
4353 return # The partial type is None.
4354 partial_types = self.find_partial_types(var)
4355 if partial_types is None:
4356 return
4357 typename = type_type.fullname
4358 if (
4359 typename == "builtins.dict"
4360 or typename == "collections.OrderedDict"
4361 or typename == "collections.defaultdict"
4362 ):
4363 # TODO: Don't infer things twice.
4364 key_type = self.expr_checker.accept(lvalue.index)
4365 value_type = self.expr_checker.accept(rvalue)
4366 if (
4367 is_valid_inferred_type(key_type)
4368 and is_valid_inferred_type(value_type)
4369 and not self.current_node_deferred
4370 and not (
4371 typename == "collections.defaultdict"
4372 and var.type.value_type is not None
4373 and not is_equivalent(value_type, var.type.value_type)
4374 )
4375 ):
4376 var.type = self.named_generic_type(typename, [key_type, value_type])
4377 del partial_types[var]
4378  
4379 def type_requires_usage(self, typ: Type) -> tuple[str, ErrorCode] | None:
4380 """Some types require usage in all cases. The classic example is
4381 an unused coroutine.
4382  
4383 In the case that it does require usage, returns a note to attach
4384 to the error message.
4385 """
4386 proper_type = get_proper_type(typ)
4387 if isinstance(proper_type, Instance):
4388 # We use different error codes for generic awaitable vs coroutine.
4389 # Coroutines are on by default, whereas generic awaitables are not.
4390 if proper_type.type.fullname == "typing.Coroutine":
4391 return ("Are you missing an await?", UNUSED_COROUTINE)
4392 if proper_type.type.get("__await__") is not None:
4393 return ("Are you missing an await?", UNUSED_AWAITABLE)
4394 return None
4395  
4396 def visit_expression_stmt(self, s: ExpressionStmt) -> None:
4397 expr_type = self.expr_checker.accept(s.expr, allow_none_return=True, always_allow_any=True)
4398 error_note_and_code = self.type_requires_usage(expr_type)
4399 if error_note_and_code:
4400 error_note, code = error_note_and_code
4401 self.fail(
4402 message_registry.TYPE_MUST_BE_USED.format(format_type(expr_type, self.options)),
4403 s,
4404 code=code,
4405 )
4406 self.note(error_note, s, code=code)
4407  
4408 def visit_return_stmt(self, s: ReturnStmt) -> None:
4409 """Type check a return statement."""
4410 self.check_return_stmt(s)
4411 self.binder.unreachable()
4412  
4413 def check_return_stmt(self, s: ReturnStmt) -> None:
4414 defn = self.scope.top_function()
4415 if defn is not None:
4416 if defn.is_generator:
4417 return_type = self.get_generator_return_type(
4418 self.return_types[-1], defn.is_coroutine
4419 )
4420 elif defn.is_coroutine:
4421 return_type = self.get_coroutine_return_type(self.return_types[-1])
4422 else:
4423 return_type = self.return_types[-1]
4424 return_type = get_proper_type(return_type)
4425  
4426 is_lambda = isinstance(self.scope.top_function(), LambdaExpr)
4427 if isinstance(return_type, UninhabitedType):
4428 # Avoid extra error messages for failed inference in lambdas
4429 if not is_lambda or not return_type.ambiguous:
4430 self.fail(message_registry.NO_RETURN_EXPECTED, s)
4431 return
4432  
4433 if s.expr:
4434 declared_none_return = isinstance(return_type, NoneType)
4435 declared_any_return = isinstance(return_type, AnyType)
4436  
4437 # This controls whether or not we allow a function call that
4438 # returns None as the expression of this return statement.
4439 # E.g. `return f()` for some `f` that returns None. We allow
4440 # this only if we're in a lambda or in a function that returns
4441 # `None` or `Any`.
4442 allow_none_func_call = is_lambda or declared_none_return or declared_any_return
4443  
4444 # Return with a value.
4445 typ = get_proper_type(
4446 self.expr_checker.accept(
4447 s.expr, return_type, allow_none_return=allow_none_func_call
4448 )
4449 )
4450  
4451 if defn.is_async_generator:
4452 self.fail(message_registry.RETURN_IN_ASYNC_GENERATOR, s)
4453 return
4454 # Returning a value of type Any is always fine.
4455 if isinstance(typ, AnyType):
4456 # (Unless you asked to be warned in that case, and the
4457 # function is not declared to return Any)
4458 if (
4459 self.options.warn_return_any
4460 and not self.current_node_deferred
4461 and not is_proper_subtype(AnyType(TypeOfAny.special_form), return_type)
4462 and not (
4463 defn.name in BINARY_MAGIC_METHODS
4464 and is_literal_not_implemented(s.expr)
4465 )
4466 and not (
4467 isinstance(return_type, Instance)
4468 and return_type.type.fullname == "builtins.object"
4469 )
4470 and not is_lambda
4471 ):
4472 self.msg.incorrectly_returning_any(return_type, s)
4473 return
4474  
4475 # Disallow return expressions in functions declared to return
4476 # None, subject to two exceptions below.
4477 if declared_none_return:
4478 # Lambdas are allowed to have None returns.
4479 # Functions returning a value of type None are allowed to have a None return.
4480 if is_lambda or isinstance(typ, NoneType):
4481 return
4482 self.fail(message_registry.NO_RETURN_VALUE_EXPECTED, s)
4483 else:
4484 self.check_subtype(
4485 subtype_label="got",
4486 subtype=typ,
4487 supertype_label="expected",
4488 supertype=return_type,
4489 context=s.expr,
4490 outer_context=s,
4491 msg=message_registry.INCOMPATIBLE_RETURN_VALUE_TYPE,
4492 )
4493 else:
4494 # Empty returns are valid in Generators with Any typed returns, but not in
4495 # coroutines.
4496 if (
4497 defn.is_generator
4498 and not defn.is_coroutine
4499 and isinstance(return_type, AnyType)
4500 ):
4501 return
4502  
4503 if isinstance(return_type, (NoneType, AnyType)):
4504 return
4505  
4506 if self.in_checked_function():
4507 self.fail(message_registry.RETURN_VALUE_EXPECTED, s)
4508  
4509 def visit_if_stmt(self, s: IfStmt) -> None:
4510 """Type check an if statement."""
4511 # This frame records the knowledge from previous if/elif clauses not being taken.
4512 # Fall-through to the original frame is handled explicitly in each block.
4513 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=False, conditional_frame=True, fall_through=0):
4514 for e, b in zip(s.expr, s.body):
4515 t = get_proper_type(self.expr_checker.accept(e))
4516  
4517 if isinstance(t, DeletedType):
4518 self.msg.deleted_as_rvalue(t, s)
4519  
4520 if_map, else_map = self.find_isinstance_check(e)
4521  
4522 # XXX Issue a warning if condition is always False?
4523 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=True, fall_through=2):
4524 self.push_type_map(if_map)
4525 self.accept(b)
4526  
4527 # XXX Issue a warning if condition is always True?
4528 self.push_type_map(else_map)
4529  
4530 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=False, fall_through=2):
4531 if s.else_body:
4532 self.accept(s.else_body)
4533  
4534 def visit_while_stmt(self, s: WhileStmt) -> None:
4535 """Type check a while statement."""
4536 if_stmt = IfStmt([s.expr], [s.body], None)
4537 if_stmt.set_line(s)
4538 self.accept_loop(if_stmt, s.else_body, exit_condition=s.expr)
4539  
4540 def visit_operator_assignment_stmt(self, s: OperatorAssignmentStmt) -> None:
4541 """Type check an operator assignment statement, e.g. x += 1."""
4542 self.try_infer_partial_generic_type_from_assignment(s.lvalue, s.rvalue, s.op)
4543 if isinstance(s.lvalue, MemberExpr):
4544 # Special case, some additional errors may be given for
4545 # assignments to read-only or final attributes.
4546 lvalue_type = self.expr_checker.visit_member_expr(s.lvalue, True)
4547 else:
4548 lvalue_type = self.expr_checker.accept(s.lvalue)
4549 inplace, method = infer_operator_assignment_method(lvalue_type, s.op)
4550 if inplace:
4551 # There is __ifoo__, treat as x = x.__ifoo__(y)
4552 rvalue_type, method_type = self.expr_checker.check_op(method, lvalue_type, s.rvalue, s)
4553 if not is_subtype(rvalue_type, lvalue_type):
4554 self.msg.incompatible_operator_assignment(s.op, s)
4555 else:
4556 # There is no __ifoo__, treat as x = x <foo> y
4557 expr = OpExpr(s.op, s.lvalue, s.rvalue)
4558 expr.set_line(s)
4559 self.check_assignment(
4560 lvalue=s.lvalue, rvalue=expr, infer_lvalue_type=True, new_syntax=False
4561 )
4562 self.check_final(s)
4563  
4564 def visit_assert_stmt(self, s: AssertStmt) -> None:
4565 self.expr_checker.accept(s.expr)
4566  
4567 if isinstance(s.expr, TupleExpr) and len(s.expr.items) > 0:
4568 self.fail(message_registry.MALFORMED_ASSERT, s)
4569  
4570 # If this is asserting some isinstance check, bind that type in the following code
4571 true_map, else_map = self.find_isinstance_check(s.expr)
4572 if s.msg is not None:
4573 self.expr_checker.analyze_cond_branch(else_map, s.msg, None)
4574 self.push_type_map(true_map)
4575  
4576 def visit_raise_stmt(self, s: RaiseStmt) -> None:
4577 """Type check a raise statement."""
4578 if s.expr:
4579 self.type_check_raise(s.expr, s)
4580 if s.from_expr:
4581 self.type_check_raise(s.from_expr, s, optional=True)
4582 self.binder.unreachable()
4583  
4584 def type_check_raise(self, e: Expression, s: RaiseStmt, optional: bool = False) -> None:
4585 typ = get_proper_type(self.expr_checker.accept(e))
4586 if isinstance(typ, DeletedType):
4587 self.msg.deleted_as_rvalue(typ, e)
4588 return
4589  
4590 exc_type = self.named_type("builtins.BaseException")
4591 expected_type_items = [exc_type, TypeType(exc_type)]
4592 if optional:
4593 # This is used for `x` part in a case like `raise e from x`,
4594 # where we allow `raise e from None`.
4595 expected_type_items.append(NoneType())
4596  
4597 self.check_subtype(
4598 typ, UnionType.make_union(expected_type_items), s, message_registry.INVALID_EXCEPTION
4599 )
4600  
4601 if isinstance(typ, FunctionLike):
4602 # https://github.com/python/mypy/issues/11089
4603 self.expr_checker.check_call(typ, [], [], e)
4604  
4605 def visit_try_stmt(self, s: TryStmt) -> None:
4606 """Type check a try statement."""
4607 # Our enclosing frame will get the result if the try/except falls through.
4608 # This one gets all possible states after the try block exited abnormally
4609 # (by exception, return, break, etc.)
4610 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=False, fall_through=0):
4611 # Not only might the body of the try statement exit
4612 # abnormally, but so might an exception handler or else
4613 # clause. The finally clause runs in *all* cases, so we
4614 # need an outer try frame to catch all intermediate states
4615 # in case an exception is raised during an except or else
4616 # clause. As an optimization, only create the outer try
4617 # frame when there actually is a finally clause.
4618 self.visit_try_without_finally(s, try_frame=bool(s.finally_body))
4619 if s.finally_body:
4620 # First we check finally_body is type safe on all abnormal exit paths
4621 self.accept(s.finally_body)
4622  
4623 if s.finally_body:
4624 # Then we try again for the more restricted set of options
4625 # that can fall through. (Why do we need to check the
4626 # finally clause twice? Depending on whether the finally
4627 # clause was reached by the try clause falling off the end
4628 # or exiting abnormally, after completing the finally clause
4629 # either flow will continue to after the entire try statement
4630 # or the exception/return/etc. will be processed and control
4631 # flow will escape. We need to check that the finally clause
4632 # type checks in both contexts, but only the resulting types
4633 # from the latter context affect the type state in the code
4634 # that follows the try statement.)
4635 if not self.binder.is_unreachable():
4636 self.accept(s.finally_body)
4637  
4638 def visit_try_without_finally(self, s: TryStmt, try_frame: bool) -> None:
4639 """Type check a try statement, ignoring the finally block.
4640  
4641 On entry, the top frame should receive all flow that exits the
4642 try block abnormally (i.e., such that the else block does not
4643 execute), and its parent should receive all flow that exits
4644 the try block normally.
4645 """
4646 # This frame will run the else block if the try fell through.
4647 # In that case, control flow continues to the parent of what
4648 # was the top frame on entry.
4649 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=False, fall_through=2, try_frame=try_frame):
4650 # This frame receives exit via exception, and runs exception handlers
4651 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=False, conditional_frame=True, fall_through=2):
4652 # Finally, the body of the try statement
4653 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=False, fall_through=2, try_frame=True):
4654 self.accept(s.body)
4655 for i in range(len(s.handlers)):
4656 with self.binder.frame_context(can_skip=True, fall_through=4):
4657 typ = s.types[i]
4658 if typ:
4659 t = self.check_except_handler_test(typ, s.is_star)
4660 var = s.vars[i]
4661 if var:
4662 # To support local variables, we make this a definition line,
4663 # causing assignment to set the variable's type.
4664 var.is_inferred_def = True
4665 self.check_assignment(var, self.temp_node(t, var))
4666 self.accept(s.handlers[i])
4667 var = s.vars[i]
4668 if var:
4669 # Exception variables are deleted.
4670 # Unfortunately, this doesn't let us detect usage before the
4671 # try/except block.
4672 source = var.name
4673 if isinstance(var.node, Var):
4674 var.node.type = DeletedType(source=source)
4675 self.binder.cleanse(var)
4676 if s.else_body:
4677 self.accept(s.else_body)
4678  
4679 def check_except_handler_test(self, n: Expression, is_star: bool) -> Type:
4680 """Type check an exception handler test clause."""
4681 typ = self.expr_checker.accept(n)
4682  
4683 all_types: list[Type] = []
4684 test_types = self.get_types_from_except_handler(typ, n)
4685  
4686 for ttype in get_proper_types(test_types):
4687 if isinstance(ttype, AnyType):
4688 all_types.append(ttype)
4689 continue
4690  
4691 if isinstance(ttype, FunctionLike):
4692 item = ttype.items[0]
4693 if not item.is_type_obj():
4694 self.fail(message_registry.INVALID_EXCEPTION_TYPE, n)
4695 return self.default_exception_type(is_star)
4696 exc_type = erase_typevars(item.ret_type)
4697 elif isinstance(ttype, TypeType):
4698 exc_type = ttype.item
4699 else:
4700 self.fail(message_registry.INVALID_EXCEPTION_TYPE, n)
4701 return self.default_exception_type(is_star)
4702  
4703 if not is_subtype(exc_type, self.named_type("builtins.BaseException")):
4704 self.fail(message_registry.INVALID_EXCEPTION_TYPE, n)
4705 return self.default_exception_type(is_star)
4706  
4707 all_types.append(exc_type)
4708  
4709 if is_star:
4710 new_all_types: list[Type] = []
4711 for typ in all_types:
4712 if is_proper_subtype(typ, self.named_type("builtins.BaseExceptionGroup")):
4713 self.fail(message_registry.INVALID_EXCEPTION_GROUP, n)
4714 new_all_types.append(AnyType(TypeOfAny.from_error))
4715 else:
4716 new_all_types.append(typ)
4717 return self.wrap_exception_group(new_all_types)
4718 return make_simplified_union(all_types)
4719  
4720 def default_exception_type(self, is_star: bool) -> Type:
4721 """Exception type to return in case of a previous type error."""
4722 any_type = AnyType(TypeOfAny.from_error)
4723 if is_star:
4724 return self.named_generic_type("builtins.ExceptionGroup", [any_type])
4725 return any_type
4726  
4727 def wrap_exception_group(self, types: Sequence[Type]) -> Type:
4728 """Transform except* variable type into an appropriate exception group."""
4729 arg = make_simplified_union(types)
4730 if is_subtype(arg, self.named_type("builtins.Exception")):
4731 base = "builtins.ExceptionGroup"
4732 else:
4733 base = "builtins.BaseExceptionGroup"
4734 return self.named_generic_type(base, [arg])
4735  
4736 def get_types_from_except_handler(self, typ: Type, n: Expression) -> list[Type]:
4737 """Helper for check_except_handler_test to retrieve handler types."""
4738 typ = get_proper_type(typ)
4739 if isinstance(typ, TupleType):
4740 return typ.items
4741 elif isinstance(typ, UnionType):
4742 return [
4743 union_typ
4744 for item in typ.relevant_items()
4745 for union_typ in self.get_types_from_except_handler(item, n)
4746 ]
4747 elif is_named_instance(typ, "builtins.tuple"):
4748 # variadic tuple
4749 return [typ.args[0]]
4750 else:
4751 return [typ]
4752  
4753 def visit_for_stmt(self, s: ForStmt) -> None:
4754 """Type check a for statement."""
4755 if s.is_async:
4756 iterator_type, item_type = self.analyze_async_iterable_item_type(s.expr)
4757 else:
4758 iterator_type, item_type = self.analyze_iterable_item_type(s.expr)
4759 s.inferred_item_type = item_type
4760 s.inferred_iterator_type = iterator_type
4761 self.analyze_index_variables(s.index, item_type, s.index_type is None, s)
4762 self.accept_loop(s.body, s.else_body)
4763  
4764 def analyze_async_iterable_item_type(self, expr: Expression) -> tuple[Type, Type]:
4765 """Analyse async iterable expression and return iterator and iterator item types."""
4766 echk = self.expr_checker
4767 iterable = echk.accept(expr)
4768 iterator = echk.check_method_call_by_name("__aiter__", iterable, [], [], expr)[0]
4769 awaitable = echk.check_method_call_by_name("__anext__", iterator, [], [], expr)[0]
4770 item_type = echk.check_awaitable_expr(
4771 awaitable, expr, message_registry.INCOMPATIBLE_TYPES_IN_ASYNC_FOR
4772 )
4773 return iterator, item_type
4774  
4775 def analyze_iterable_item_type(self, expr: Expression) -> tuple[Type, Type]:
4776 """Analyse iterable expression and return iterator and iterator item types."""
4777 iterator, iterable = self.analyze_iterable_item_type_without_expression(
4778 self.expr_checker.accept(expr), context=expr
4779 )
4780 int_type = self.analyze_range_native_int_type(expr)
4781 if int_type:
4782 return iterator, int_type
4783 return iterator, iterable
4784  
4785 def analyze_iterable_item_type_without_expression(
4786 self, type: Type, context: Context
4787 ) -> tuple[Type, Type]:
4788 """Analyse iterable type and return iterator and iterator item types."""
4789 echk = self.expr_checker
4790 iterable: Type
4791 iterable = get_proper_type(type)
4792 iterator = echk.check_method_call_by_name("__iter__", iterable, [], [], context)[0]
4793  
4794 if (
4795 isinstance(iterable, TupleType)
4796 and iterable.partial_fallback.type.fullname == "builtins.tuple"
4797 ):
4798 return iterator, tuple_fallback(iterable).args[0]
4799 else:
4800 # Non-tuple iterable.
4801 iterable = echk.check_method_call_by_name("__next__", iterator, [], [], context)[0]
4802 return iterator, iterable
4803  
4804 def analyze_range_native_int_type(self, expr: Expression) -> Type | None:
4805 """Try to infer native int item type from arguments to range(...).
4806  
4807 For example, return i64 if the expression is "range(0, i64(n))".
4808  
4809 Return None if unsuccessful.
4810 """
4811 if (
4812 isinstance(expr, CallExpr)
4813 and isinstance(expr.callee, RefExpr)
4814 and expr.callee.fullname == "builtins.range"
4815 and 1 <= len(expr.args) <= 3
4816 and all(kind == ARG_POS for kind in expr.arg_kinds)
4817 ):
4818 native_int: Type | None = None
4819 ok = True
4820 for arg in expr.args:
4821 argt = get_proper_type(self.lookup_type(arg))
4822 if isinstance(argt, Instance) and argt.type.fullname in MYPYC_NATIVE_INT_NAMES:
4823 if native_int is None:
4824 native_int = argt
4825 elif argt != native_int:
4826 ok = False
4827 if ok and native_int:
4828 return native_int
4829 return None
4830  
4831 def analyze_container_item_type(self, typ: Type) -> Type | None:
4832 """Check if a type is a nominal container of a union of such.
4833  
4834 Return the corresponding container item type.
4835 """
4836 typ = get_proper_type(typ)
4837 if isinstance(typ, UnionType):
4838 types: list[Type] = []
4839 for item in typ.items:
4840 c_type = self.analyze_container_item_type(item)
4841 if c_type:
4842 types.append(c_type)
4843 return UnionType.make_union(types)
4844 if isinstance(typ, Instance) and typ.type.has_base("typing.Container"):
4845 supertype = self.named_type("typing.Container").type
4846 super_instance = map_instance_to_supertype(typ, supertype)
4847 assert len(super_instance.args) == 1
4848 return super_instance.args[0]
4849 if isinstance(typ, TupleType):
4850 return self.analyze_container_item_type(tuple_fallback(typ))
4851 return None

4854 self, index: Expression, item_type: Type, infer_lvalue_type: bool, context: Context
4855 ) -> None:
4856 """Type check or infer for loop or list comprehension index vars."""
4857 self.check_assignment(index, self.temp_node(item_type, context), infer_lvalue_type)

4859 def visit_del_stmt(self, s: DelStmt) -> None:
4860 if isinstance(s.expr, IndexExpr):
4861 e = s.expr
4862 m = MemberExpr(e.base, "__delitem__")
4863 m.line = s.line
4864 m.column = s.column
4865 c = CallExpr(m, [e.index], [nodes.ARG_POS], [None])
4866 c.line = s.line
4867 c.column = s.column
4868 self.expr_checker.accept(c, allow_none_return=True)
4869 else:
4870 s.expr.accept(self.expr_checker)
4871 for elt in flatten(s.expr):
4872 if isinstance(elt, NameExpr):
4873 self.binder.assign_type(
4874 elt, DeletedType(source=elt.name), get_declaration(elt), False
4875 )
